<h2 id="head-fd3469ef997b41f5632f8fe81c8124cbd6783d12">Thunderlord Demonologist</h2>
<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>:  My demonologist is now clev 33, and specializing in swordmastery and demonology.  I have symbiosis (.4) and mindcraft (.5) as well, so I've got some options as to where I spend my skill points. 
</p>
<p>
I have the full gothmog armoury at the moment, so it's pretty cool to have <em>all the spoily info</em> on them. 
</p>
<p>
I want:  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 50 swordmastery 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 40 demonology   (summon greater demons) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 20 prayer       (tulkas -- devine aim + demonblade) 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
That's my main focus, but i'd like 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 12 Monster lore (get some companions from my summons) as well 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Other skills I am considering to pump 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Magic 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Mindcraft 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Symbiosis 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Spirituality 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Combat 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Weaponmastery 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
My first beastmaster quest is a shadow drake, and I am not sure if they drop corpses, but I haven't even run into any of them yet, so I don't think I can bargain on that much monster lore from him. 
</p>
<p>
I don't know how much I'll be able to do with prayer, but I've done 2 quests, but haven't received the next one yet.  <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/sad.png" alt=":(" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ZV">ZV</a>: If you are willing to exploit the fact that restoring life levels may net you god quests (using junkarts &amp; potions from temple), you will get all five god quests [if it is still valid in 2.3]. As you'll be summoning with demonology, I don't see much point in pumping symbiosis up. You could get some weaponmastery, a few points, though not too much, as pumping swordmastery will give you about enough weaponmastery. As for mindcraft, if you don't have good source of detection, few points can help. Having reliable source of monster detection, you may go on hunting trip for beastmaster monsters. It's best to do it all at once, when your clvl isn't too high, so you can get easier quests. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a>: Sorryto break it to you:  from the 2.2.7 changelog; <pre>[B]- Scumming for god quests (by losing and regaining xp) is now prevented. 
     -- fearoffours</pre>
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Reenen's still got a chance at getting a few more God quests, though. I've never played a Demonologist, but I agree with Zasvid: A few points of Mindcraft never hurt, especially if you have no other means of detection. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>: Mindcraft has a couple of things I really want (though I am a thunderlord so the teleports are only nice) 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Trap detection (need 5) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 ESP temp (need 25) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Minor teleport (need 3, or 25 for voidgates)  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Major teleport (need 7) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Character Armor (13) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Adreneline channeling (23) 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
So it's either 5, or 25.  I've got 5 already. Another 20 will cost me 40 skill points.  I dunno if it's worth it.  It's 40 that could go to Magic (more mana), or combat/weaponmastery (I am a warrior after all), or whatever other skills. 
</p>
